    "plan_content": "## Plan: Add `Bun.INI` namespace\n\nHere's what I found and how I plan to implement it:\n\n### What Exists\n- Internal INI parser at `src/ini.zig` (used by npm config, not exposed publicly)\n- Pattern to follow: `JSON5Object.zig` (parse + stringify), `TOMLObject.zig` (parse only)\n- The wiring chain: `api.zig` â†’ `BunObject.zig` â†’ `BunObject+exports.h` â†’ `BunObject.cpp`\n\n### 6 Files to Change\n\n| # | File | Change |\n|---|------|--------|\n| 1 | **CREATE** `src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig` | New self-contained `create`, `parse`, `stringify` |\n| 2 | `src/bun.js/api.zig` | Add `pub const INIObject = @import(\"./api/INIObject.zig\");` |\n| 3 | `src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig` | Add import, `pub const INI = toJSLazyPropertyCallback(Bun.getINIObject);`, and getter function |\n| 4 | `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h` | Add `macro(INI)` between `Glob` and `JSON5` |\n| 5 | `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp` | Add `INI BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI DontDelete|PropertyCallback` to `bunObjectTable` |\n| 6 | `packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts` | Add `namespace INI { parse(...); stringify(...); }` after `JSONC` block |\n\n### INI Semantics\n- **parse**: Line-by-line; `[section]` â†’ nested object; `key = value` (whitespace trimmed); `;`/`#` comments; throws on malformed lines\n- **stringify**: Global primitives first as `key = value`, then `[section]` blocks for object values; throws on 2-level-deep nesting\n- Implementation is **self-contained** in `INIObject.zig` â€” does not import `src/ini.zig`",
